Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_physical_partitions(25.10)            create_physical_partitions(25.10)

Name
       create_physical_partitions  -  Creates  temporary logic hierarchies for
       hierarchical placement and routing implementation based on the existing
       cell and macro placement or based on  the  specified  hierarchical  in-
       stances and/or instances

Syntax
       create_physical_partitions

       [-help]

       {{<partition_spec> | -logical_spec <spec>}

       [-group_instance_suffix <string>]

       [-check_only]

       [[-undo [-pre_full_upf <string >[-incremental_block_upfs <string>]]]]}

       Creates  temporary  logic  hierarchies  for  hierarchical placement and
       routing implementation based on the existing cell and  macro  placement
       or  based on the specified hierarchical instances and/or instances. The
       create_physical_partitions command automatically  modifies/updates  the
       SDC, UPF, TCF, and Scan-Chain.

       It supports:

              * Cutting a partition into two

              * Merging two partitions into one

              * Mixing and matching partitions

       Note: To create a new hierarchy, some hinsts may be ungrouped and their
       referenced hinsts and hpins in all collaterals may become invalid.

       Note:  Once  the original hierarchies are ungrouped, they cannot be re-
       covered back.

       This command is a limited-access feature in this release. It is enabled
       by a variable specified through the setLimitedAccessFeature command. To
       use this feature, contact your Cadence representative to  explain  your
       usage  requirements, and make sure this feature meets your needs before
       deploying it widely.

Parameters
       -check_only
              Checks the constraints consistency  for  creating  new  physical
              partitions.  It  detects potential problems and reports error(s)
              with UPF/SDC/hier PG connection.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -group_instance_suffix <string>
              Specifies the group instance suffix. This suffix is added to the
              generated hinst name.

              Default: i

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each create_physical_partitions parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man create_physical_partitions

       -incremental_block_upfs <string>
              Specifies extra UPFs during top and block implementations.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -logical_spec <spec>
              Creates  new  logical  hierarchy  based  on the specified hinsts
              and/or instances.

              The specification must be specified in the following format:

              -logical_spec { newHierName1 {instName1 instName2 ..  hinstName1
              hinstName2 instName3 ...}

                              newHierName2  {instName1 instName2 .. hinstName1
              hinstName2 instName3 ...} }

              Note: The parent hierarchy of hinsts and/or  instances  included
              in the logical spec is ungrouped.

              Note: If the create_physical_partitions command is used with the
              -logical_spec parameter, partitions are not defined.

              Data_type: string, optional

       <partition_spec>
              Defines the name and boundary of new physical partition(s).

              The specification must be specified in the following format:

              {<newHierName1>  {<boxes  list1>} <newHierName2> {<boxes list2>}
              ...}

              Note: When undoing a physical partition, if there is a  conflict
              with instance names:

              * The first hinst that is undone will not have a prefix.

              * In  case of a name conflict, the instance name will be renamed
                to <<instName>>_<<hinstName>>_<<index>>.

              For example, if the instance name is i1  inside  a  hinst  named
              acc2,  then when you ungroup or undo acc2, any conflict will re-
              sult in renaming this instance i1 to i1_acc2_1.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -pre_full_upf <string>
              Specifies the original full-chip UPFs that are available  before
              calling  the  create_physical_partitions  command  for the first
              time to create physical hierarchies.

              Note: For designs that have power domains, this  parameter  must
              be specified.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -undo  Undo physical partitions.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * You  can  define  the  names  and  boundaries (abutted or non-
                abutted) of new physical partitions in the following format:

                set phys_ptn_spec {

                  acc_sm2   {258.0000000000    16.1500000000    458.6000000000
                459.0400000000}

                  acc_sm1    {17.8000000000    16.1500000000    258.0000000000
                459.0400000000}

                }

              *

                The following command creates physical  partitions  using  the
                phys_ptn_spec defined earlier:

                create_physical_partitions $phys_ptn_spec

              * The following command undos the physical partitions:

                create_physical_partitions $phys_ptn_spec -undo

Related Information
